## Current state (last verified: 2026-06-18)
- Phase: 2 - Subscription management UI
- Stripe webhook handler complete and tested
- Working on the plan management page next

## Active task (WIP = 1)
Building the plan selection UI component - /src/components/PlanSelector.tsx

## Decisions log (last verified: 2026-06-18)
| Date | Decision | Rationale |
|------|----------|-----------|
| 2026-06-17 | Use Stripe Customer Portal for billing management | Avoids building custom billing UI, PCI compliant |
| 2026-06-16 | Zustand for state management, not Redux | Simpler API, less boilerplate for this scale |
| 2026-06-15 | Deploy on Vercel, DB on PlanetScale | Both have good free tiers for early stage |

## Learnings and gotchas (last verified: 2026-06-18)
- Stripe webhooks require raw body parsing - do NOT use express.json() on the webhook route
- PlanetScale schema changes need a separate deploy step before code deploy
- The Stripe test mode key starts with sk_test_ - never use live keys in development

## Open questions
- Do we need a free tier or is the paid-only model fine for launch?
- Should plan upgrades be prorated or take effect next billing cycle?
